subSubSection.paragraph:
Colouration. Labrum black. Males: humeral spots present, large discal spot with anterior margin straight and reaching apex of scutellum, anterolaterally regularly emarginate around humeral spot, lateral margin parallel, posterior margin slightly oblique with outer angle more produced behind (
Fig. 32
). Females: large discal spot covering also humeral part of elytra (
Fig. 33
).

Head (
Fig. 15
) dull, with large frontal impression covered with large punctures, vertex covered with large punctures mixed with small punctures. Anterior clypeal processes subtriangular, very wide, short, robust, clypeal margin between processes shallowly bisinuate. Mandibles wide, moderately rounded, with sharp dorsal keel. Only inner slopes of mandibles visible in dorsal view.

Aedeagus (
Fig. 3
). Dorsal impression small, ca as long as wide. Apex with triangular, somewhat elevated folds separated with parallel furrow. Ventral side with narrow shallow impression along anterior margin and with two small, elongate, shallow impressions in middle part.

Everted aedeagus (
Fig. 21
). Ejaculatory guide W-shaped in dorsal view, lateral branches connected by very narrow semicircular conjunction, in lateral view ear-like. Lateral sclerites large. Anterior sclerite relatively narrow, forming two concave plates connected in basal suture.

Spermatheca (
Fig. 9
). Vasculum widely round, apical part gradualy narrowed towards shortly round apex, basal part wide. Bulbus very small. Ductus spermathecae twice as long as vasculum, coiled in whole lenght, coils more frequent towards the base.
